This paper deals with coding schemes for reliable communication over packet networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper presents a capacity-achieving coding scheme and derives error exponents to quantify the rate of error decay. The next likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with packet networks and extends the network model to allow for different arrival processes. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility, as the paper deals with multicast communication. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely but still possible categories, as the paper presents a coding scheme that achieves capacity and deals with the complexity of decoding.
